review_blob: This is a superbly superior brew, hands down~ Good job "Founders", Good Job!
I could imbibe in this brew with consistent interest. My comments arent as a palate expert of the wicked-weed known as hops. I enjoy as a hobby.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - The Calling IPA

review_blob: No doubt a quaffable brew; although light, which for me puts it in an all-day IPA realm.
I was always skeptical in regards to a gluten free brew, but when i saw Wicked Weed with it I figured it was the one to try. I wasnt let down; as its another outstanding brew from the Weed~

I was very impressed with the brewers ability to mask an alcohol by volume of 10+% with absolutely no overbearing effect on the smooth and inviting flavours that flow through the pallet. Good job "Canton Brewing".

I find the flavour very European/German. It reminds me of two of my favorite German brews from Hacker-Pschorr (Weissebier), and a pale ale brewed by Kstritzer. Way to go Stone, another fine example of perfection.
The aroma to me has a resin-hay, sorta. Slightly sulfur. With a 10% ABV it is super smooth; as I dont note the biting, bitter on the tongue as described on the label.

Not sure what idiots they had rating this before; as I can only assume they were all domestic beer aficionados! This is very aromatic, with the proper arrangments of hops and malts, otherwise A VERY GOOD BEER.....
I rate it as a standard taste and aroma for a decent IPA. I am impressed at how well they hid the 10% ABV.
I have no way to rate it any lower than the highest rating,,,,,,,,, It is the best for my taste, check it out.
beer_name: NoDa Hop, Drop n Roll IPA
